n each target for 10 seconds to verify no immediate crashes:\n  ```bash\n  cargo +nightly fuzz run fuzz_wire_payload -- -max_total_time=10\n  cargo +nightly fuzz run fuzz_outer_envelope -- -max_total_time=10\n  cargo +nightly fuzz run fuzz_inner_envelope -- -max_total_time=10\n  cargo +nightly fuzz run fuzz_tombstone -- -max_total_time=10\n  ```\n- [ ] **Step 2:** If any target finds a crash, investigate and fix before committing\n\n## Task 5: CI workflow\n\n**File:** `.github/workflows/fuzz.yml`\n\n```yaml\nname: Fuzz\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [master]\n  schedule:\n    - cron: '42 3 * * 1'  # Weekly Monday 3:42 AM\n\njobs:\n  fuzz:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        target: [fuzz_wire_payload, fuzz_outer_envelope, fuzz_inner_envelope, fuzz_tombstone]\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: dtolnay/rust-toolchain@nightly\n      - run: cargo install cargo-fuzz\n      - run: cargo +nightly fuzz run ${{ matrix.target }} -- -max_total_time=60\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 1:** Create `.github/workflows/fuzz.yml`\n- [ ] **Step 2:** Verify YAML is valid with `actionlint`\n\n## Task 6: Commit and push\n\n- [ ] **Step 1:** Commit: `feat: add cargo-fuzz harnesses for wire format parsing`\n- [ ] **Step 2:** Push and create PR closing #125\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Check targets exist\ncargo +nightly fuzz list\n\n# Build all targets\ncargo +nightly fuzz build\n\n# Smoke test (10s each)\ncargo +nightly fuzz run fuzz_wire_payload -- -max_total_time=10\ncargo +nightly fuzz run fuzz_outer_envelope -- -max_total_time=10\ncargo +nightly fuzz run fuzz_inner_envelope -- -max_total_time=10\ncargo +nightly fuzz run fuzz_tombstone -- -max_total_time=10\n\n# Existing tests still pass\ncargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets\n\n# CI lint still passes\nactionlint .github/workflows/fuzz.yml\n```\n\n---\n\n# (Previous plans below — completed)\n\n# Make encode paths return Result (#123)\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Remove panic paths from wire format serialization by making encode methods return `Result`.\n\n**Architecture:** Change 4 methods in `reme-message` to return `Result`, propagate at 9 production call sites (all already in `Result`-returning functions), update tests.\n\n**Tech Stack:** No new deps. Uses existing `postcard::Error`.\n\n---\n\n## Context\n\nIssue #123 tracks `.unwrap()` panics in the message send path. The postcard migration (PR #141) preserved these panics 1:1 from bincode. PR reviewers flagged it. The review document lists this as priority 10.\n\nWhile postcard serialization of known fixed types practically cannot fail, the infallible API signatures hide a panic path. Library code should not panic — callers should decide how to handle errors.\n\n---\n\n## What changes\n\n### 1. `WirePayload::encode()` — the main target\n\n**File:** `crates/reme-message/src/wire.rs:68-81`\n\nChange signature from `fn encode(&self) -> Vec<u8>` to `fn encode(&self) -> Result<Vec<u8>, postcard::Error>`.\n\nReplace `.unwrap()` with `?`.\n\n**9 production callers** — all already return `Result<_, TransportError>` or `Result<_, String>`:\n- `crates/reme-transport/src/mqtt.rs:405,427`\n- `crates/reme-transport/src/http_target.rs:460,496`\n- `crates/reme-transport/src/mqtt_target.rs:284,316`\n- `crates/reme-transport/src/http.rs:498,550`\n- `apps/node/src/api.rs:370`\n\nEach caller needs `.map_err(|e| ...)` to convert `postcard::Error` → their error type.\n\n**Test callers** (just add `.unwrap()`):\n- `crates/reme-message/src/wire.rs:132` (unit test)\n- `crates/reme-message/tests/golden_wire_format.rs:451,475`\n- `crates/reme-transport/src/http_target.rs:668` (test helper)\n- `crates/reme-transport/src/http.rs:1062` (test helper)\n- `apps/node/tests/receipt_on_submit.rs:144`\n- `apps/client/src/tui/http_server.rs` (7 test functions)\n\n### 2. `SignedAckTombstone::to_wire_bytes()` and `to_bytes()`\n\n**File:** `crates/reme-message/src/tombstone.rs:178-187`\n\nChange both to return `Result<Vec<u8>, postcard::Error>`. **Zero production callers** — only used in tests. Test callers just add `.unwrap()`.\n\n### 3. `OuterEnvelope::to_bytes()`\n\n**File:** `crates/reme-message/src/lib.rs:185`\n\n**Dead code** — zero callers anywhere. Change to return `Result` for consistency, or remove entirely.\n\n### 4. `TransportError` variant\n\n`crates/reme-transport/src/lib.rs` (or wherever `TransportError` is defined) — check if it already has a serialization error variant. If not, add one.\n\n---\n\n## Steps\n\n- [ ] **Step 1:** Change `WirePayload::encode()` signature to `Result<Vec<u8>, postcard::Error>`, replace `.unwrap()` with `?`\n- [ ] **Step 2:** Change `SignedAckTombstone::to_wire_bytes()` and `to_bytes()` to return `Result`\n- [ ] **Step 3:** Change `OuterEnvelope::to_bytes()` to return `Result` (or remove if dead code)\n- [ ] **Step 4:** Update all 9 production callers with error mapping\n- [ ] **Step 5:** Update all test callers with `.unwrap()`\n- [ ] **Step 6:** Run `cargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets`\n- [ ] **Step 7:** Run `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`\n- [ ] **Step 8:** Commit\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\ncargo fmt --all -- --check\ncargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings\ncargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets\n```\n\nAll 580+ tests pass, zero clippy warnings, zero `.unwrap()` on `postcard::to_allocvec` in non-test code.\n\n---\n\n# (Previous plan below — Bincode to Postcard Migration — completed)\n\n# Bincode to Postcard Migration Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Replace bincode v2 with postcard for all wire format serialization, gaining serde-based derives and a documented wire format spec.\n\n**Architecture:** Bottom-up migration following crate dependency order: reme-identity -> reme-message -> reme-encryption -> reme-node-core/reme-core -> cleanup. Each crate is migrated and tested independently before moving to dependents.\n\n**Tech Stack:** `postcard ^1.1` (with `alloc` feature), `serde ^1.0` (with `derive` feature)\n\n---\n\n## Context\n\nThe ROADMAP calls for migrating from bincode to postcard before v0.5 (sneakernet). Bincode v2 uses Rust-specific `Encode`/`Decode` traits requiring manual impls for custom types. Postcard uses serde (`Serialize`/`Deserialize`), which is the Rust ecosystem standard, has a [documented wire format spec](https://postcard.jamesmunns.com), and works well for embedded/constrained transports (BLE, LoRa). This migration also prepares the codebase for the eventual v1.0 Protobuf migration by establishing serde as the serialization foundation.\n\nBreaking changes are explicitly OK — no deployed clients exist.\n\n---\n\n## Dependency order\n\n```\nreme-identity          (leaf)\n  -> reme-message      (depends on reme-identity)\n       -> reme-encryption  (depends on reme-message)\n       -> reme-node-core   (depends on reme-message)\n       -> reme-core        (depends on reme-message, reme-encryption)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Add postcard to workspace deps\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `Cargo.toml` (workspace root, line 37)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add postcard workspace dep**\n\n  Add after `bincode` line:\n  ```toml\n  postcard = { version = \"^1.1\", features = [\"alloc\"] }\n  ```\n  Keep `bincode` for now (removed in Task 7).\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Verify workspace resolves**\n\n  Run: `cargo check --workspace 2>&1 | head -5`\n  Expected: compiles (postcard added but unused)\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Commit**\n\n  ```\n  chore: add postcard workspace dependency\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Migrate reme-identity\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/reme-identity/Cargo.toml`\n- Modify: `crates/reme-identity/src/lib.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Update Cargo.toml**\n\n  Replace `bincode = { workspace = true }` with:\n  ```toml\n  postcard = { workspace = true }\n  serde = { workspace = true, features = [\"derive\"] }\n  ```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Replace bincode imports with serde**\n\n  Remove lines 1-4:\n  ```rust\n  use bincode::de::Decoder;\n  use bincode::enc::Encoder;\n  use bincode::error::{DecodeError, EncodeError};\n  use bincode::{impl_borrow_decode, Decode, Encode};\n  ```\n  Add:\n  ```rust\n  use serde::{Deserialize, Deserializer, Serialize, Serializer};\n  ```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Change RoutingKey derive**\n\n  At `RoutingKey` struct (line ~224), replace `Encode, Decode` with `Serialize, Deserialize`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Replace PublicID manual impls**\n\n  Replace the manual `Encode`/`Decode` impls and `impl_borrow_decode!` (lines 280-294) with:\n\n  ```rust\n  impl Serialize for PublicID {\n      fn serialize<S: Serializer>(&self, serializer: S) -> Result<S::Ok, S::Error> {\n          self.to_bytes().serialize(serializer)\n      }\n  }\n\n  impl<'de> Deserialize<'de> for PublicID {\n      fn deserialize<D: Deserializer<'de>>(deserializer: D) -> Result<Self, D::Error> {\n          let bytes = <[u8; 32]>::deserialize(deserializer)?;\n          Self::try_from_bytes(&bytes).map_err(serde::de::Error::custom)\n      }\n  }\n  ```\n\n  **Critical:** This preserves the security invariant — low-order X25519 points are rejected on deserialization.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run tests**\n\n  Run: `cargo test -p reme-identity`\n  Expected: all pass\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n  ```\n  refactor: migrate reme-identity from bincode to postcard/serde\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Migrate reme-message\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/reme-message/Cargo.toml`\n- Modify: `crates/reme-message/src/lib.rs`\n- Modify: `crates/reme-message/src/tombstone.rs`\n- Modify: `crates/reme-message/src/wire.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Update Cargo.toml**\n\n  Replace `bincode = { workspace = true }` with:\n  ```toml\n  postcard = { workspace = true }\n  serde = { workspace = true, features = [\"derive\"] }\n  ```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Replace imports in lib.rs**\n\n  Remove lines 1-3 (bincode imports). Add:\n  ```rust\n  use serde::{Deserialize, Deserializer, Serialize, Serializer};\n  ```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Remove `bincode_config()` function**\n\n  Delete the `bincode_config()` function and its doc comment (lines 43-61). This was re-exported to reme-encryption.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Replace MessageID manual impls**\n\n  Replace lines 97-113 with:\n  ```rust\n  impl Serialize for MessageID {\n      fn serialize<S: Serializer>(&self, serializer: S) -> Result<S::Ok, S::Error> {\n          self.0.as_bytes().serialize(serializer)\n      }\n  }\n\n  impl<'de> Deserialize<'de> for MessageID {\n      fn deserialize<D: Deserializer<'de>>(deserializer: D) -> Result<Self, D::Error> {\n          let bytes = <[u8; 16]>::deserialize(deserializer)?;\n          Ok(MessageID(Uuid::from_bytes(bytes)))\n      }\n  }\n  ```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Change all derive macros in lib.rs**\n\n  Replace `Encode, Decode` with `Serialize, Deserialize` on:\n  - `Version` (line 129)\n  - `OuterEnvelope` (line 154)\n  - `InnerEnvelope` (line 217)\n  - `Content` (line 318)\n  - `TextContent` (line 325)\n  - `ReceiptContent` (line 331)\n  - `ReceiptKind` (line 337)\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Replace encode/decode calls in lib.rs**\n\n  `OuterEnvelope::to_bytes()` (line 213):\n  ```rust\n  postcard::to_allocvec(self).expect(\"envelope serialization\")\n  ```\n\n  `InnerEnvelope::content_id()` (line 291):\n  ```rust\n  let content_bytes = postcard::to_allocvec(&self.content)\n      .expect(\"content serialization\");\n  ```\n\n  Test `test_dag_fields_serialization` (lines ~588-590):\n  ```rust\n  let bytes = postcard::to_allocvec(&inner).unwrap();\n  let decoded: InnerEnvelope = postcard::from_bytes(&bytes).unwrap();\n  ```\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Migrate tombstone.rs**\n\n  Replace `use bincode::{Decode, Encode};` with `use serde::{Serialize, Deserialize};`.\n\n  Change `SignedAckTombstone` derive from `Encode, Decode` to `Serialize, Deserialize`.\n\n  Replace serialization calls:\n  - `to_wire_bytes()`: `postcard::to_allocvec(self).unwrap()`\n  - `to_bytes()`: `postcard::to_allocvec(self).unwrap()`\n  - `from_bytes()`: `postcard::from_bytes(bytes).map_err(|e| ...)`\n\n  Note: `test_ack_tombstone_size` asserts 96 bytes. Postcard serializes `[u8; N]` as raw N bytes and structs with no framing — total should remain 96 bytes (16 + 16 + 64). Run test to confirm.\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Migrate wire.rs**\n\n  Replace all `bincode::encode_to_vec(...)` with `postcard::to_allocvec(...)`.\n\n  Replace `bincode::decode_from_slice(...)` with `postcard::from_bytes(...)`.\n\n  Note: `from_bytes` is strict about trailing bytes. The wire format is `[type: u8][exact payload]` so this should be fine. If transport padding causes issues, switch to `postcard::take_from_bytes` instead.\n\n  Update module doc comment: `bincode bytes` -> `postcard bytes`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 9: Run tests**\n\n  Run: `cargo test -p reme-message`\n  Expected: all pass\n\n- [ ] **Step 10: Commit**\n\n  ```\n  refactor: migrate reme-message from bincode to postcard/serde\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Migrate reme-encryption\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/reme-encryption/Cargo.toml`\n- Modify: `crates/reme-encryption/src/lib.rs`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Update Cargo.toml**\n\n  Replace `bincode = { workspace = true }` with:\n  ```toml\n  postcard = { workspace = true }\n  serde = { workspace = true, features = [\"derive\"] }\n  ```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Remove bincode_config import**\n\n  In `lib.rs` line 7, change:\n  ```rust\n  use reme_message::{bincode_config, InnerEnvelope, MessageID, ACK_HASH_DOMAIN};\n  ```\n  to:\n  ```rust\n  use reme_message::{InnerEnvelope, MessageID, ACK_HASH_DOMAIN};\n  ```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Replace error types**\n\n  Rep