, port, max_messages, tls_*, rate_limit_*, mqtt_*, auth_*, storage_path, etc.) into `ServeArgs`\n- Keep `config` and `log_level` as global on `Cli`\n- Add `storage_path` to global args too (needed by export/import to find the DB)\n- `ExportArgs`: file, routing_key (Option<String>), force, limit (Option<usize>), since (Option<String>)\n- `ImportArgs`: file\n- In `main.rs`: dispatch `None | Some(Commands::Serve(_))` → existing server startup; `Export` → stub; `Import` → stub (stubs replaced in Tasks 2 and 3)\n\nAfter this task: `reme-node` still starts the server, `reme-node serve` does the same, `reme-node export/import --help` show options.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Read config.rs thoroughly** — understand all CliArgs fields and load_config()\n- [ ] **Step 2: Create Cli/Commands/ServeArgs/ExportArgs/ImportArgs structs**\n- [ ] **Step 3: Refactor load_config into load_config_from(cli, serve_args)**\n- [ ] **Step 4: Update main.rs to dispatch subcommands**\n- [ ] **Step 5: Add tests for CLI parsing**\n- [ ] **Step 6: Verify: `cargo test -p node && cargo clippy -p node --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`**\n- [ ] **Step 7: Commit**\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Add `get_all_messages` to PersistentMailboxStore + implement node export (#187)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/reme-node-core/src/mailbox_store.rs` — add `get_all_messages()` and `get_messages_by_routing_key()` methods\n- Create: `apps/node/src/export.rs` — export logic\n- Modify: `apps/node/src/main.rs` — wire export\n- Modify: `apps/node/Cargo.toml` — add humantime\n\nThe node export is simpler than the client export because:\n- No identity needed (node stores opaque envelopes)\n- No Client construction\n- `envelope_data` in the DB is already postcard-serialized `OuterEnvelope`\n- WirePayload encoding: deserialize OuterEnvelope from DB bytes, wrap in `WirePayload::Message`, encode\n\nNew `PersistentMailboxStore` methods needed:\n```rust\n/// Get all non-expired messages across all routing keys.\npub fn get_all_messages(&self) -> Result<Vec<OuterEnvelope>, NodeError>\n\n/// Get all non-expired messages for a specific routing key.\npub fn get_messages_by_routing_key(&self, routing_key: &RoutingKey) -> Result<Vec<OuterEnvelope>, NodeError>\n```\n\n`ExportArgs` fields (from Task 1):\n- `file: PathBuf`\n- `routing_key: Option<String>` (hex-encoded 16-byte RoutingKey)\n- `force: bool`\n- `limit: Option<usize>`\n- `since: Option<String>` (humantime duration)\n\nExport flow:\n1. Open `PersistentMailboxStore::open(storage_path, config)`\n2. Query: `get_all_messages()` or `get_messages_by_routing_key(rk)`\n3. Apply --since and --limit filters (OuterEnvelope has no created_at... check the DB)\n4. For each envelope: `WirePayload::Message(envelope).encode()` → write frame\n5. Write bundle via BundleWriter\n6. Print summary\n\nNote: `OuterEnvelope` doesn't have a `created_at` field. The `created_at` is in the DB `mailbox_messages` table. So for --since filtering, we need to return `(OuterEnvelope, i64)` pairs from the store method, or filter in SQL.\n\nBetter approach: filter in SQL. Add optional `since_secs` and `limit` params to the store methods:\n```rust\npub fn export_messages(\n    &self,\n    routing_key: Option<&RoutingKey>,\n    since_secs: Option<i64>,\n    limit: Option<usize>,\n) -> Result<Vec<OuterEnvelope>, NodeError>\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `export_messages()` to PersistentMailboxStore**\n- [ ] **Step 2: Create `apps/node/src/export.rs`**\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add humantime to node Cargo.toml**\n- [ ] **Step 4: Wire export in main.rs**\n- [ ] **Step 5: Add tests**\n- [ ] **Step 6: Verify: `cargo test --workspace && cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`**\n- [ ] **Step 7: Commit**\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Implement node import (#188)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `apps/node/src/import.rs` — import logic\n- Modify: `apps/node/src/main.rs` — wire import\n\nNode import is simpler than client import:\n- No identity, no decryption, no Client\n- Just `MailboxStore::enqueue(routing_key, envelope)` for messages (INSERT OR IGNORE = idempotent)\n- For tombstones: `store.get_ack_hash(message_id)` → `tombstone.verify_authorization(&ack_hash)` → `store.delete_message(message_id)` (same as API handler)\n\nImport flow:\n1. Open `PersistentMailboxStore::open(storage_path, config)`\n2. Read bundle via BundleReader, verify checksum\n3. For each frame:\n   - `WirePayload::Message(envelope)` → `store.enqueue(envelope.routing_key, envelope)` — dedup via INSERT OR IGNORE\n   - `WirePayload::AckTombstone(tombstone)` → verify authorization against stored ack_hash, delete if valid\n4. Print summary: `Imported N messages (M tombstones applied, K duplicates, E errors)`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Create `apps/node/src/import.rs`**\n- [ ] **Step 2: Wire import in main.rs**\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add tests**\n- [ ] **Step 4: Verify: `cargo test --workspace && cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`**\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Full workspace verification\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: `cargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets`**\n- [ ] **Step 2: `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`**\n- [ ] **Step 3: `cargo fmt --all -- --check`**\n",
