            "prompt": "You are implementing three node-side issues for the reme project: #186 (subcommands), #187 (export), #188 (import).\n\nProject: /home/leon0399/Projects/reme/.claude/worktrees/feat-186-node-subcommands/\n\nRead the plan at `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-03-28-node-subcommands-export-import.md` for context.\n\n## What to implement\n\n### Part 1: Restructure node binary with clap subcommands (#186)\n\nMirror the client approach from `apps/client/src/config.rs` (read it to see the pattern).\n\nIn `apps/node/src/config.rs`:\n1. Read the existing `CliArgs` struct carefully (it has ~35 fields for server args)\n2. Create a new `Cli` struct with `Option<Commands>` subcommand and global args (`config`, `log_level`, `storage_path`)\n3. Create `Commands` enum: `Serve(ServeArgs)`, `Export(ExportArgs)`, `Import(ImportArgs)`\n4. Move ALL server-specific args from `CliArgs` into `ServeArgs` (bind_addr, port, max_messages, default_ttl, node_id, peers, cleanup_*, auth_*, rate_limit_*, tls_*, mqtt_*, identity_path, public_host, additional_hosts, allow_insecure_destination, max_body_size, max_batch_size)\n5. `ExportArgs`: `file: PathBuf`, `routing_key: Option<String>`, `force: bool`, `limit: Option<usize>`, `since: Option<String>`\n6. `ImportArgs`: `file: PathBuf`\n7. Refactor `load_config()` into `load_config_from(cli: &Cli, serve_args: Option<&ServeArgs>)` — same pattern as client\n8. Add `Cli::serve_args()` helper method\n\nIn `apps/node/src/main.rs`:\n1. Parse `Cli`, extract serve_args, call `load_config_from`\n2. Dispatch: `None | Some(Commands::Serve(_))` → existing server startup; `Export` → `export::run_export()`; `Import` → `import::run_import()`\n3. Add `mod export;` and `mod import;`\n\n### Part 2: Add export_messages to PersistentMailboxStore + implement node export (#187)\n\nIn `crates/reme-node-core/src/mailbox_store.rs`, add to `impl PersistentMailboxStore`:\n```rust\n/// Export messages with optional filters. Used by `reme-node export`.\npub fn export_messages(\n    &self,\n    routing_key: Option<&RoutingKey>,\n    since_secs: Option<i64>,\n    limit: Option<usize>,\n) -> Result<Vec<OuterEnvelope>, NodeError> {\n    let conn = self.conn.lock().map_err(|_| NodeError::LockPoisoned)?;\n    \n    // Build dynamic SQL with optional WHERE clauses\n    let mut sql = String::from(\n        \"SELECT envelope_data FROM mailbox_messages WHERE expires_at > ?\"\n    );\n    let now = now_secs();\n    let mut params: Vec<Box<dyn rusqlite::types::ToSql>> = vec![Box::new(now)];\n    \n    if let Some(rk) = routing_key {\n        sql.push_str(\" AND routing_key = ?\");\n        params.push(Box::new(rk.as_bytes().to_vec()));\n    }\n    if let Some(since) = since_secs {\n        sql.push_str(\" AND created_at >= ?\");\n        params.push(Box::new(since));\n    }\n    sql.push_str(\" ORDER BY created_at ASC\");\n    if let Some(lim) = limit {\n        sql.push_str(&format!(\" LIMIT {lim}\"));\n    }\n    \n    let param_refs: Vec<&dyn rusqlite::types::ToSql> = params.iter().map(|p| p.as_ref()).collect();\n    let mut stmt = conn.prepare(&sql)?;\n    let rows = stmt.query_map(param_refs.as_slice(), |row| {\n        row.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(0)\n    })?;\n    \n    let mut envelopes = Vec::new();\n    for row in rows {\n        let data = row?;\n        match postcard::from_bytes::<OuterEnvelope>(&data) {\n            Ok(env) => envelopes.push(env),\n            Err(e) => {\n                tracing::warn!(\"Skipping corrupt envelope in mailbox: {e}\");\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    Ok(envelopes)\n}\n```\n\nNote: Check how `now_secs()` is defined in the file (it's a helper returning current Unix seconds).\n\nAdd `humantime` to `apps/node/Cargo.toml`:\n```toml\nhumantime = { workspace = true }\n```\n\nCreate `apps/node/src/export.rs`:\n```rust\nuse crate::config::{ExportArgs, NodeConfig};\nuse reme_bundle::BundleWriter;\nuse reme_identity::RoutingKey;\nuse reme_message::wire::WirePayload;\nuse reme_node_core::PersistentMailboxStore;\nuse std::fs;\nuse std::sync::Arc;\nuse std::time::{Duration, SystemTime, UNIX_EPOCH};\n\npub fn run_export(\n    config: &NodeConfig,\n    store: &PersistentMailboxStore,\n    args: &ExportArgs,\n) -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\n    // Check output path\n    if args.file.exists() && !args.force {\n        return Err(format!(\n            \"Output file '{}' already exists. Use --force to overwrite.\",\n            args.file.display()\n        ).into());\n    }\n\n    // Parse --routing-key filter\n    let routing_key_filter = args.routing_key.as_deref().map(parse_routing_key).transpose()?;\n    \n    // Parse --since filter\n    let since_secs = args.since.as_deref().map(parse_since).transpose()?;\n\n    // Query messages\n    let envelopes = store.export_messages(\n        routing_key_filter.as_ref(),\n        since_secs,\n        args.limit,\n    )?;\n\n    if envelopes.is_empty() {\n        if args.force && args.file.exists() {\n            fs::remove_file(&args.file)?;\n        }\n        eprintln!(\"Nothing to export.\");\n        return Ok(());\n    }\n\n    // Write bundle\n    let file = fs::File::create(&args.file)?;\n    let mut writer = BundleWriter::new(file);\n    let mut count = 0;\n    for env in &envelopes {\n        let wire = WirePayload::Message(env.clone());\n        match wire.encode() {\n            Ok(frame) => {\n                writer.write_frame(&frame)?;\n                count += 1;\n            }\n            Err(e) => {\n                eprintln!(\"Warning: skipping message: {e}\");\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    writer.finish()?;\n\n    eprintln!(\"Exported {count} messages to {}\", args.file.display());\n    Ok(())\n}\n\nfn parse_routing_key(hex_str: &str) -> Result<RoutingKey, Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\n    if hex_str.len() != 32 {\n        return Err(format!(\n            \"Invalid routing key: expected 32 hex characters (16 bytes), got {}\",\n            hex_str.len()\n        ).into());\n    }\n    let bytes = hex::decode(hex_str)\n        .map_err(|e| format!(\"Invalid routing key: bad hex encoding: {e}\"))?;\n    let bytes: [u8; 16] = bytes.try_into()\n        .expect(\"32 hex chars always decode to 16 bytes\");\n    Ok(RoutingKey::from(bytes))\n}\n\nfn parse_since(since_str: &str) -> Result<i64, Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\n    let duration: Duration = humantime::parse_duration(since_str)\n        .map_err(|e| format!(\"Invalid --since duration '{since_str}': {e}\"))?;\n    let now = SystemTime::now()\n        .duration_since(UNIX_EPOCH)\n        .map_err(|_| \"System time before Unix epoch\")?\n        .as_secs();\n    Ok((now.saturating_sub(duration.as_secs())) as i64)\n}\n```\n\nIMPORTANT: Check how `RoutingKey` is constructed. Look at `reme-identity/src/lib.rs` for `RoutingKey` — it may have `from_bytes`, `From<[u8; 16]>`, or a constructor. Also check `RoutingKey::as_bytes()` for the SQL param. Adapt the code accordingly.\n\n### Part 3: Implement node import (#188)\n\nCreate `apps/node/src/import.rs`:\n- Read bundle, verify checksum\n- For `WirePayload::Message(envelope)`: `store.enqueue(envelope.routing_key, envelope)` — dedup via INSERT OR IGNORE\n- For `WirePayload::AckTombstone(tombstone)`: verify against `store.get_ack_hash(&tombstone.message_id)`, delete if valid, skip if not found\n- Print summary\n\n```rust\nuse crate::config::{ImportArgs, NodeConfig};\nuse reme_bundle::BundleReader;\nuse reme_message::wire::WirePayload;\nuse reme_node_core::PersistentMailboxStore;\nuse std::fs::File;\n\n#[derive(Default)]\nstruct ImportSummary {\n    stored: usize,\n    duplicates: usize,\n    tombstones_applied: usize,\n    tombstones_skipped: usize,\n    errors: usize,\n}\n\npub fn run_import(\n    config: &NodeConfig,\n    store: &PersistentMailboxStore,\n    args: &ImportArgs,\n) -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\n    if !args.file.exists() {\n        return Err(format!(\"Bundle file '{}' not found.\", args.file.display()).into());\n    }\n\n    // Read and verify bundle\n    let frames = read_bundle(&args.file)?;\n    if frames.is_empty() {\n        eprintln!(\"Nothing to import (empty bundle).\");\n        return Ok(());\n    }\n\n    let mut summary = ImportSummary::default();\n    for (i, frame) in frames.iter().enumerate() {\n        match WirePayload::decode(frame) {\n            Ok(WirePayload::Message(envelope)) => {\n                // Check for duplicate first\n                if store.has_message(&envelope.routing_key, &envelope.message_id)? {\n                    summary.duplicates += 1;\n                    continue;\n                }\n                match store.enqueue(envelope.routing_key, envelope) {\n                    Ok(()) => summary.stored += 1,\n                    Err(e) => {\n                        eprintln!(\"Warning: frame {i}: failed to store: {e}\");\n                        summary.errors += 1;\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            Ok(WirePayload::AckTombstone(tombstone)) => {\n                match store.get_ack_hash(&tombstone.message_id) {\n                    Ok(Some(ack_hash)) => {\n                        if tombstone.verify_authorization(&ack_hash) {\n                            match store.delete_message(&tombstone.message_id) {\n                                Ok(_) => summary.tombstones_applied += 1,\n                                Err(e) => {\n                                    eprintln!(\"Warning: frame {i}: tombstone delete failed: {e}\");\n                                    summary.errors += 1;\n                                }\n                            }\n                        } else {\n                            eprintln!(\"Warning: frame {i}: tombstone authorization failed\");\n                            summary.errors += 1;\n                        }\n                    }\n                    Ok(None) => {\n                        // Message not found or already deleted — skip silently\n                        summary.tombstones_skipped += 1;\n                    }\n                    Err(e) => {\n                        eprintln!(\"Warning: frame {i}: tombstone lookup failed: {e}\");\n                        summary.errors += 1;\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n            Err(e) => {\n                eprintln!(\"Warning: frame {i}: failed to decode: {e}\");\n                summary.errors += 1;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    print_summary(&summary);\n    Ok(())\n}\n\nfn read_bundle(path: &std::path::Path) -> Result<Vec<Vec<u8>>, Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\n    let file = File::open(path)?;\n    let mut reader = BundleReader::open(file)?;\n    let mut frames = Vec::new();\n    while let Some(frame) = reader.next_frame()? {\n        frames.push(frame);\n    }\n    reader.verify_checksum()?;\n    Ok(frames)\n}\n\nfn print_summary(s: &ImportSummary) {\n    let mut parts = Vec::new();\n    if s.stored > 0 { parts.push(format!(\"{} stored\", s.stored)); }\n    if s.duplicates > 0 { parts.push(format!(\"{} duplicates skipped\", s.duplicates)); }\n    if s.tombstones_applied > 0 { parts.push(format!(\"{} tombstones applied\", s.tombstones_applied)); }\n    if s.tombstones_skipped > 0 { parts.push(format!(\"{} tombstones skipped (not found)\", s.tombstones_skipped)); }\n    if s.errors > 0 { parts.push(format!(\"{} errors\", s.errors)); }\n    if parts.is_empty() {\n        eprintln!(\"Nothing to import.\");\n    } else {\n        eprintln!(\"Import complete: {}\", parts.join(\", \"));\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIMPORTANT notes:\n- `MailboxStore::enqueue` takes `(RoutingKey, OuterEnvelope)` — the routing_key comes from `envelope.routing_key`\n- `MailboxStore::has_message` takes `(&RoutingKey, &MessageID)` — check exact signature\n- `SignedAckTombstone::verify_authorization` takes `&[u8; 16]` (the ack_hash) — verify the exact method signature\n- For the export, `store.export_messages()` needs to return data from the DB — check the exact column names and how `postcard::from_bytes` is used elsewhere in the file for deserialization\n- The node's `main.rs` needs to open the store BEFORE dispatching to export/import. Look at how the existing main.rs opens the store and pass it to the export/import functions.\n- For export/import in main.rs, the store needs to be opened with the same config as serve mode. Extract the store-opening logic.\n\n### Wiring in main.rs\n\nThe existing main.rs flow:\n1. `load_config()` → `NodeConfig`\n2. Load identity\n3. Open `PersistentMailboxStore`\n4. Start server\n\nFor subcommand dispatch:\n- `Serve` / `None` → full existing flow (identity, store, server)\n- `Export` → open store (no identity needed), call `export::run_export(config, store, args)`\n- `Import` → open store (no identity needed), call `import::run_import(config, store, args)`\n\nThe store opening logic should be shared. The `PersistentStoreConfig` can be derived from `NodeConfig`.\n\n### Final verification\n\nAfter all three parts:\n1. `cargo fmt --all`\n2. `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`\n3. `cargo test --workspace --all-features --all-targets`\n\nFix any issues. Do NOT leave failing tests or clippy warnings.\n",
