er is a manually re-implemented version of what `tui-popup` provides.\n- Verdict: **use it**. Every popup is currently ~15–30 lines of manual `Clear` + `Layout::vertical([Constraint::Length(height)]).flex(Flex::Center)` — exactly what `tui-popup` abstracts.\n\n**tui-scrollview** (`0.6.2`, joshka)\n- What reme needs it for: message view scrolling. Currently `render_messages` builds a flat `Vec<Line>`, renders it as a `Paragraph::scroll((app.message_scroll, 0))`, and the scroll offset is a manual `u16` bumped by key events. This breaks for long message histories.\n- Maintained: yes — same maintainer as tui-popup, actively updated.\n- Overlap: none.\n- v0.5 relevance: moderate — the import summary (M duplicates, K relayed) could also benefit from a scrollable result list if import is large.\n- Verdict: **worth adopting**, especially once message history grows beyond what fits in a screen. The current `Paragraph::scroll` approach does not handle variable-height content correctly.\n\n**throbber-widgets-tui** (`0.11.0`)\n- What reme needs it for: the \"sending...\" state on messages is currently a static italic string. v0.5 adds progress feedback during export/import. A spinner would improve perceived responsiveness.\n- Maintained: 0.11.0 is fairly recent. Not as actively maintained as joshka's crates but still updated.\n- Overlap: none.\n- v0.5 relevance: **directly useful** — export/import are async operations. The plan explicitly calls for \"progress indicator during export/import.\"\n- Verdict: **adopt for v0.5**. Lightweight, no conflict with existing code.\n\n**ratatui-toaster** (`0.1.2`)\n- What reme needs it for: non-blocking status notifications. Currently, all feedback writes to `app.status: String` on the one-line status bar, which gets overwritten immediately. Events like \"message sent\", \"upstream added\", \"import complete\" all stomp each other.\n- Maintained: 0.1.2 — very small, alpha-quality (0.1.x). The fact that it describes itself as \"extremely lightweight\" is code for \"minimal features.\"\n- Overlap: none directly, but `app.status` is the incumbent.\n- v0.5 relevance: yes — import results (\"N imported, M skipped\") are a natural toast candidate.\n- Verdict: **consider, but not a priority.** It's 0.1.x, sparse API. You could get equivalent value by promoting `app.status` to a `VecDeque<(String, Instant)>` with time-based expiry, which you control. That's ~20 lines. Only adopt this if you want something off-the-shelf and are comfortable with the immaturity.\n\n**tui-widget-list** (`0.15.0`)\n- What reme needs it for: the conversation list currently uses ratatui's built-in `List`. `tui-widget-list` supports arbitrary heterogeneous items with per-item height — useful if you want a richer conversation list (preview line, unread badge, avatar) rather than flat `ListItem`.\n- Maintained: 0.15.0, active.\n- Overlap: directly overlaps with the existing `List`. Not a drop-in replacement — it's a different API.\n- v0.5 relevance: none.\n- Verdict: **low priority now, potential future upgrade.** The conversation list is currently simple enough that the built-in `List` is fine. Revisit when implementing rich message previews or per-item expand/collapse.\n\n---\n\n#### SKIP (reason given)\n\n**ratatui-explorer** (`0.3.0`)\n- v0.5 adds file path *input*, not a full filesystem *browser*. The export/import popups want a single-line text field pre-populated with a default path, not a tree explorer.\n- A full file explorer widget is UI pattern mismatch for a messaging app — users won't expect ncdu-style navigation to pick a file in a chat app.\n- Verdict: **skip**. The existing `tui-textarea` single-line input is the right tool for file path entry.\n\n**rat-widget** (`3.2.1`, thscharler)\n- A comprehensive all-in-one suite including text-input, date/number input, textarea, checkbox, file-dialog, menubar, status-bar, table.\n- The file-dialog component sounds relevant for v0.5. However, the suite is designed as a cohesive ecosystem — adopting just one component likely means dragging in the whole suite.\n- It is actively maintained (3.2.1 is recent) but the API is less documented than joshka's crates and the ecosystem coupling is high.\n- Verdict: **skip for now.** reme only needs the file-dialog piece, and `rat-widget`'s advantage (breadth) is not needed. Individual focused crates are lower risk.\n\n**edtui** (`0.11.2`)\n- Vim-inspired modal editor widget. reme uses `tui-textarea` for message input and single-line text fields. Vim modal editing (insert/normal/visual modes) is a dramatic UX shift for a messaging client's input box.\n- Users do not expect modal editing when typing chat messages.\n- Verdict: **skip**. Not appropriate for a messaging input model.\n\n**ratatui-textarea** (fork of tui-textarea)\n- reme already uses `tui-textarea`. `ratatui-textarea` is a fork with minor differences (e.g., naming conventions). There is no feature reme needs that tui-textarea lacks.\n- Switching forks mid-project creates churn for no gain.\n- Verdict: **skip**. Stay on `tui-textarea`.\n\n**tui-dialog** (`?`)\n- Single-line text input dialog. `tui-textarea` already covers this. Redundant.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**tui-prompts** (`0.6.1`)\n- Interactive prompts (text, password, confirm). reme already uses `tui-textarea` for text input and `rpassword` for password input. `tui-prompts` would be redundant.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**tui-logger** (`0.18.1`)\n- A logger that routes `tracing`/`log` output into a ratatui widget panel. reme is a messaging client with a single-window layout — there is no persistent log pane, nor is there a good place to put one without splitting the layout.\n- Verdict: **skip** for the TUI. It could be marginally useful in a debug mode or dev build, but it's not worth the layout complexity for end users.\n\n**tui-menu** (`0.3.1`)\n- A menu widget (menubar-style). reme's navigation is keyboard-driven with keybindings listed in the status bar. A visual menu widget doesn't fit this model and would take up screen real estate.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**tui-tree-widget** (not in search results — likely stale or renamed)\n- Contact management in reme is a flat list of direct contacts. No tree hierarchy is needed.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**tui-checkbox** (`?`)\n- No current or planned feature in reme requires checkbox widgets.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**tui-big-text** (`?`)\n- Large text display. No use case in a messaging client TUI.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**tui-input** (`0.15.0`, headless)\n- A headless input library (no rendering, just input state management). reme uses `tui-textarea` which handles both input state and rendering. `tui-input` would require writing custom rendering code on top.\n- Verdict: **skip**. No benefit over `tui-textarea` for reme's use case.\n\n**tui-slider** (`?`)\n- No use case in reme.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n**ratatui-code-editor** (`?`)\n- Code editor with tree-sitter. reme is a messaging app, not a code editor.\n- Verdict: **skip**.\n\n---\n\n### Prioritized adoption recommendation for v0.5\n\n| Priority | Crate | Why now |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `tui-popup` | 6 popups exist or will exist in v0.5. The hand-rolled approach is already duplicating code. |\n| 2 | `throbber-widgets-tui` | v0.5 explicitly requires progress feedback during export/import operations. |\n| 3 | `tui-scrollview` | Message history scrolling is fragile today; adopt before history gets long. |\n| 4 | `ratatui-toaster` | Low priority — assess only if the `app.status` string approach becomes a real UX problem during v0.5. |\n\nThe rest are either redundant with existing deps, wrong UX paradigm for a messaging app, or too immature to take a dependency on.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>46736</total_tokens><tool_uses>14</tool_uses><duration_ms>100959</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-reme/cde6fd4c-88a8-464b-941a-e71717209706/tasks/a3e28562bf7830ef6.output",
