            "command": "gh issue create \\\n  --title \"refactor: replace show_*_popup bools with PopupKind enum\" \\\n  --milestone \"v0.5: Sneakernet Export\" \\\n  --label \"enhancement\" \\\n  --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\nReplace 4 separate `show_*_popup` bools with a single `active_popup: Option<PopupKind>` enum. Required before v0.5 TUI integration adds 2 more popups (export/import).\n\n## Problem\n\nPR #163 established the Action-based architecture but left popup state management unchanged:\n\n- `show_add_contact_popup: bool` (line 416)\n- `show_my_id_popup: bool` (line 420)\n- `show_add_upstream_popup: bool` (line 422)\n- `show_upstreams_popup: bool` (line 426)\n\n`handle_key_event()` dispatches via sequential `if` chain (lines 1268-1279):\n\n```rust\nif self.show_add_contact_popup {\n    return self.handle_popup_key_event(key);\n}\nif self.show_my_id_popup {\n    return self.handle_my_id_popup_key_event(key);\n}\nif self.show_add_upstream_popup {\n    return self.handle_add_upstream_popup_key_event(key);\n}\nif self.show_upstreams_popup {\n    return self.handle_upstreams_popup_key_event(key);\n}\n```\n\nAdding v0.5 export/import popups would mean 6 bools and 6 branches.\n\nAdditionally, every popup-open action is written **twice** — once in the `Alt+key` block and once in the `F(N)` fallback block (lines 1293-1354). Same `self.show_X = true; self.X_popup.reset(); self.status = \"...\"` duplicated.\n\n## Solution\n\n```rust\nenum PopupKind {\n    AddContact(AddContactPopup),\n    MyIdentity,\n    AddUpstream(AddUpstreamPopup),\n    ViewUpstreams,\n    Export(ExportPopup),    // v0.5\n    Import(ImportPopup),    // v0.5\n}\n\n// Replaces all 4 show_* bools:\nactive_popup: Option<PopupKind>,\n```\n\nDispatch becomes a single `match`:\n\n```rust\nif let Some(popup) = &mut self.active_popup {\n    match popup {\n        PopupKind::AddContact(p) => p.handle_key(key),\n        PopupKind::MyIdentity => self.handle_my_id_popup_key_event(key),\n        // .