            "content": "## Summary\n\nThe standalone `node` binary should advertise itself via mDNS so clients on the LAN can discover it without manual configuration.\n\n## Background\n\nCurrently, mDNS is only wired into the client (`apps/client/src/discovery/`). The standalone `node` binary has no mDNS support — clients must manually configure `[[peers.http]]` entries to reach it.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAfter binding the HTTP server, the node optionally advertises itself as `_reme._tcp.local.` using `MdnsSdBackend::start_advertising()` from `reme-discovery`. TXT records include:\n- `v=1` — protocol version\n- `rk=<routing_key_hex>` — node's routing key (from identity)\n- `port=<http_port>` — bound HTTP port\n- `caps=relay,store` — capability tokens (forward-compatible for v0.7+)\n\nClients already know how to discover `_reme._tcp.local.` services and verify via `/api/v1/identity` challenge-response. This issue only adds the node-side advertisement — no changes to client discovery.\n\n## Configuration\n\n```toml\n[lan_discovery]\nenabled = false  # default: off for standalone nodes\n```\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n1. Add `reme-discovery` as a dependency to `apps/node`\n2. After HTTP server bind, call `MdnsSdBackend::start_advertising()` with bound address + TXT records\n3. Requires node identity loaded (`identity_path` config) for routing_key in TXT\n4. Wire graceful shutdown of mDNS backend via existing `CancellationToken`\n5. `caps` TXT field is new — add to `reme-discovery` TXT helpers\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Node with `lan_discovery.enabled = true` is discoverable by clients via mDNS\n- TXT records include `v`, `rk`, `port`, `caps`\n- Node without identity loaded: mDNS advertisement skipped with warning\n- Graceful shutdown stops mDNS advertisement\n- No peer discovery or verification from node side (that's a separate issue)\n\n## Related\n\n- Client-side discovery: `apps/client/src/discovery/`\n- Discovery backend: `crates/reme-discovery/`\n- #10