            "content": "# Re-process existing mDNS peers when a new contact is added\n\n**Issue:** #100\n**Date:** 2026-03-27\n**Status:** Design approved\n\n## Problem\n\nmDNS `PeerDiscovered` events are effectively one-shot per session (~56 min TTL). When a peer is discovered before its routing key exists in the contact list, the controller discards it with \"Ignoring stranger.\" If the user later adds that peer as a contact, the peer is never re-processed — direct LAN messaging won't work until the peer restarts or the mDNS cache expires.\n\n**Failure scenario:**\n\n| Time | Event | Result |\n|------|-------|--------|\n| T=0 | Client starts, `contact_index` empty | — |\n| T=1 | mDNS: Peer X advertises `rk_X` | `PeerDiscovered` emitted |\n| T=2 | Controller: `contact_index.get(&rk_X)` → None | \"Ignoring stranger\" — data discarded |\n| T=3 | User adds Peer X as contact | `contact_index` updated, but no peer data left |\n| T=∞ | Peer X stuck until mDNS TTL expires or peer restarts | No direct transport registered |\n\n## Design: Stranger cache\n\n### Data structure\n\nAdd `stranger_cache: HashMap<String, RawDiscoveredPeer>` to `DiscoveryController`, keyed by mDNS instance name (consistent with `peer_index`).\n\nThe routing key is already encoded in `RawDiscoveredPeer`'s TXT records, extractable via `decode_txt()`.\n\n### Flow changes\n\n**On `PeerDiscovered`/`PeerUpdated` — routing key not in `contact_index`:**\n\nInstead of discarding, insert into `stranger_cache`. If cache size exceeds `max_peers`, drop the new entry (simple cap, no eviction complexity needed — strangers are transient).\n\n**On `PeerLost`:**\n\nRemove from `stranger_cache` by instance name, in addition to existing `peer_index` cleanup.\n\n**On `contact_rx` — new contact added:**\n\nAfter inserting into `contact_index`, scan `stranger_cache` for peers whose decoded routing key matches the new contact's routing key. For each match:\n1. Remove from `stranger_cache`\n2. Feed into the existing `handle_discovered()` method\n\nThis triggers identity verification and transport registration — the same flow as a fresh discovery.\n\n### Scope\n\n- **Changed file:** `apps/client/src/discovery/controller.rs` only\n- **No changes to:** `DiscoveryBackend` trait, `MdnsSdBackend`, `AdvertisementSpec`, `discovery/mod.rs`, config, wire format\n- **No new config options** — reuses `max_peers` for the cache cap\n\n### Testing\n\n1. **Stranger cached then matched:** Discover peer → verify it's cached (not in `peer_index`) → add contact with matching routing key → verify peer gets processed and appears in `peer_index`\n2. **PeerLost cleans stranger cache:** Discover peer (stranger) → `PeerLost` → verify cache is empty\n3. **Cache respects max_peers:** Fill cache to `max_peers` → discover one more stranger → verify cache doesn't grow beyond cap\n\n### What this does NOT change\n\n- mDNS backend or `DiscoveryBackend` trait\n- Identity verification protocol\n- Transport registration logic\n- Config surface\n- Wire format\n",
